      <section eId="sec_748">
        <num>748</num>
        <heading>Adjournment of fact-finding hearing</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_748__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>If the respondent is\nin pre-dispositional placement, the court may adjourn a fact-finding\nhearing\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_748__subsec_i">
          <num>(i)</num>
          <content>
            <p>on its own motion or on motion of the petitioner for good cause\nshown for not more than three days;\n  (ii) on motion on behalf of the respondent or by his or her parent or\nother person legally responsible for his or her care for good cause\nshown, for a reasonable period of time.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_748__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Successive motions to adjourn a fact-finding hearing may be\ngranted only under special circumstances.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_748__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>The court shall state on the record the reason for any adjournment\nof the fact-finding hearing.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
